references.paper_title: Masked Autoencoders Enable Efficient Knowledge Distillers
references.reason: This paper introduces the core method of knowledge distillation used to create the compact gaze estimation model in GazeGen.

references.paper_title: On-Device Few-Shot Personalization for Real-Time Gaze Estimation
references.reason: This paper is highly relevant due to its focus on personalized gaze estimation, a key feature of GazeGen.

references.paper_title: A Differential Approach for Gaze Estimation
references.reason: This paper presents a method for gaze estimation that is relevant to GazeGen's real-time gaze prediction capabilities.

references.paper_title: ConvNeXt V2: Co-designing and Scaling ConvNets with Masked Autoencoders
references.reason: This paper provides the foundational architecture (ConvNeXt V2) used as the teacher network for knowledge distillation in GazeGen.
This paper introduces FastSAM, a crucial component used in GazeGen for efficient object detection and mask generation.
